WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:03.171
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system,

00:03.204 --> 00:05.439
sexually based offenses are
considered especially heinous.

00:05.473 --> 00:07.708
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:07.741 --> 00:09.577
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:09.610 --> 00:11.179
are members of an elite squad

00:11.212 --> 00:13.047
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:13.081 --> 00:18.052
These are their stories.

00:18.086 --> 00:19.587
I don't care how much
money I'll make.

00:19.620 --> 00:20.454
I'm going to med school.

00:20.488 --> 00:22.190
You're not going
to make the big bucks

00:22.223 --> 00:24.458
working at an HMO,
and those loans...

00:24.492 --> 00:26.194
Why do we have
to be rich?

00:26.227 --> 00:27.728
I want my life
to be meaningful.

00:27.761 --> 00:30.064
Oh, so suddenly having money
isn't be meaningful?

00:30.098 --> 00:34.068
I love you, but
your values suck.

00:34.102 --> 00:36.504
( woman shrieking )
Oh, my God...

00:38.239 --> 00:39.673
Kyle!

00:41.375 --> 00:42.743
Kyle, be careful!

00:46.380 --> 00:48.216
Kyle!

00:48.249 --> 00:49.617
BAMFORD:
Folks over there say

00:49.650 --> 00:51.752
she came running
down the street already on fire.

00:51.785 --> 00:53.221
And you're thinking
it's a rape.

00:53.254 --> 00:54.622
That's why I called
the panty police.

00:54.655 --> 00:56.490
Found her torn underwear
in that doorway.

00:56.524 --> 00:58.759
Guy must've ripped 'em off
before he torched her.

00:58.792 --> 01:00.228
She's pretty crispy.

01:00.261 --> 01:01.762
Any prayer of
getting DNA?

01:01.795 --> 01:04.665
Only if you have a special
connection upstairs.

01:04.698 --> 01:07.635
With any luck, the lab'll find
something on the underwear.

01:07.668 --> 01:08.769
The guy was careless.

01:08.802 --> 01:10.504
Maybe he left
something else behind.

01:10.538 --> 01:12.373
Looks like there's blood
on that pipe.

01:12.406 --> 01:14.375
He could've hit her
on the head with it.

01:14.408 --> 01:16.110
STABLER:
Smells like fuel oil.

01:16.144 --> 01:18.246
You'd have to add an accelerant
to light her up.

01:18.279 --> 01:20.381
We'll run a gas chromo,
see what he used.

01:20.414 --> 01:23.517
BENSON:
Well, there's no
mailing labels on
these magazines,

01:23.551 --> 01:26.387
but we got a register receipt.

01:26.420 --> 01:28.522
Time stamp says 7:14.

01:28.556 --> 01:31.525
Witnesses said they saw her
around 7:40,

01:31.559 --> 01:33.794
so maybe she bought
the magazines nearby.

01:33.827 --> 01:35.796
We find the newsstand.
Or better yet,
get prints.

01:35.829 --> 01:37.398
Any I.D.? Purse?

01:37.431 --> 01:40.134
Fire melted it
onto her body.

01:40.168 --> 01:43.137
I've never seen
a woman raped and
then burned alive.

01:43.171 --> 01:45.706
Guy's looking
to send a message.

01:47.208 --> 01:51.412
Captioning sponsored by
UNIVERSAL NETWORK TELEVISION

01:51.445 --> 01:54.215
and NBC

02:32.753 --> 02:33.721
Whoever you're looking for

02:33.754 --> 02:34.622
is sicker than I thought.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.290
Setting her on fire
isn't sick enough?

02:36.324 --> 02:37.425
Not for this guy.

02:37.458 --> 02:38.826
There are pubic hairs
in that blood.

02:38.859 --> 02:40.428
He raped her
with a pipe.

02:40.461 --> 02:42.963
To be sure, I stained
the skin cells

02:42.996 --> 02:45.299
scraped off the metal;
they're cervical.

02:45.333 --> 02:46.467
VICAP should be able
to tell us

02:46.500 --> 02:48.702
if there're any rapists out
there who uses foreign objects

02:48.736 --> 02:49.503
and burns their victim.

02:49.537 --> 02:51.572
He didn't burn
quite all of her.

02:51.605 --> 02:52.840
She was wearing
high boots.

02:52.873 --> 02:55.309
You see that? It's
made from henna.

02:55.343 --> 02:56.109
STABLER:
Some tattoo.

02:56.143 --> 02:58.312
Drawn on the skin
and set with oil.

02:58.346 --> 03:00.448
It's a traditional
Muslim design

03:00.481 --> 03:02.316
for weddings and
family celebrations.

03:02.350 --> 03:03.851
Only Muslim?
Mostly.

03:03.884 --> 03:07.488
You see it in Africa, India
and all over the Middle East.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.591
Burning Muslims?
Could be a hate crime.

03:10.624 --> 03:11.725
Let's not say that
too loud.

03:11.759 --> 03:13.461
Last thing we need
is copycats.

03:13.494 --> 03:14.395
STABLER:
Nothing from VICAP.

03:14.428 --> 03:15.996
The only burnings
of women we could find

03:16.029 --> 03:17.465
are by men in India
when their wives

03:17.498 --> 03:18.466
don't play by the rules.

03:18.499 --> 03:19.600
Yeah, like
having an affair.

03:19.633 --> 03:21.001
Husband's family
helps do the burning.

03:21.034 --> 03:22.336
An angry husband
makes sense,

03:22.370 --> 03:23.737
especially if his
wife cheated on him.

03:23.771 --> 03:25.339
CRAGEN:
That would cover a lot of men.

03:25.373 --> 03:26.607
He burned her alive.

03:26.640 --> 03:27.741
What does that tell you?

03:27.775 --> 03:29.610
Fire's a form
of purification.

03:29.643 --> 03:31.612
We burn witches,
garbage,

03:31.645 --> 03:33.881
anything that makes us
feel evil or dirty...

03:33.914 --> 03:36.350
and, of course, fire's
a metaphor for passion.

03:36.384 --> 03:38.486
Freud believed
that setting fires

03:38.519 --> 03:39.553
was a sign
of disturbed

03:39.587 --> 03:40.821
adolescent sexuality.

03:40.854 --> 03:44.525
Maybe we're dealing with a man
who still lives with his mother.

03:44.558 --> 03:45.526
MUNCH:
We found the guy

03:45.559 --> 03:46.427
who sold her
the magazines.

03:46.460 --> 03:48.362
Doesn't remember
what she looked like,

03:48.396 --> 03:50.364
what she said,
or if she was with anyone,

03:50.398 --> 03:51.932
and considering
what he was snorting,

03:51.965 --> 03:53.634
it's a miracle
he remembers his own name.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.636
CRAGEN:
Whatever this is,
let's be careful
not to say

03:55.669 --> 03:57.771
Muslim men like
to burn their wives.

03:57.805 --> 03:59.039
No, if they want
to burn people,

03:59.072 --> 04:00.908
they fly a airplane
full of gasoline

04:00.941 --> 04:03.377
into an office building.
Excuse me,

04:03.411 --> 04:05.479
but they were extremists.
( phone rings )

04:05.513 --> 04:07.381
Sorry, but my next door
neighbor's Iranian.

04:07.415 --> 04:08.649
At airports,
even he's scared

04:08.682 --> 04:10.050
when he sees
Middle Eastern passports.

04:10.083 --> 04:11.385
I mean, let's get real.

04:11.419 --> 04:12.920
People know it's wrong,
but they think it

04:12.953 --> 04:15.523
anyway.
STABLER:
Okay, thanks.

04:15.556 --> 04:16.657
Lab caught us a break.

04:16.690 --> 04:18.892
CRAGEN:
Talk to them.

04:18.926 --> 04:21.061
The prints on the magazines
are smudged,

04:21.094 --> 04:22.530
basically useless.

04:22.563 --> 04:23.731
Is that the good news?

04:23.764 --> 04:27.935
Be patient. Her
purse burned with
everything inside.

04:27.968 --> 04:29.937
We tested the
ash residue.

04:29.970 --> 04:33.807
It was made of suede,
and we were able to
clean up the label.

04:33.841 --> 04:35.409
STABLER:
"Lant-ve-lyn"?

04:35.443 --> 04:36.677
BENSON:
Probably a private label.

04:36.710 --> 04:38.412
That's what
I was thinking.

04:38.446 --> 04:40.414
Okay, I give up.
Private label?

04:40.448 --> 04:42.082
Well, small stores
go to manufacturers

04:42.115 --> 04:43.817
who provide them
with custom labels

04:43.851 --> 04:46.687
to make it look like the purse
was made only for that store.

04:46.720 --> 04:51.659
Now, I'm guessing
that the "lyn"... is Brooklyn.

04:51.692 --> 04:54.462
Indian or Middle Eastern
neighborhoods in Brooklyn.

04:56.029 --> 04:59.833
Atlantic Avenue?

05:02.470 --> 05:06.374
Let's see if somebody there
recognizes the tattoo.

05:06.407 --> 05:08.709
It's beautiful, but
it's not my work,

05:08.742 --> 05:10.444
and this wasn't done
by an Indian.

05:10.478 --> 05:11.979
Do you have any idea
who might've done it?

05:12.012 --> 05:13.981
Someone from Egypt,
I would think.

05:14.014 --> 05:16.984
See the narrow penpoint style,
the detailing?

05:17.017 --> 05:20.454
Zara? Hey, Zara.

05:20.488 --> 05:21.722
Zara, come look.

05:21.755 --> 05:23.591
Is this your work?

05:23.624 --> 05:25.125
They're police officers.

05:25.158 --> 05:26.727
Of course,
I did that.

05:26.760 --> 05:28.662
Aha, I thought so.
It's lovely.

05:28.696 --> 05:30.664
Do you remember
who you did it for?

05:30.698 --> 05:33.000
Mira Elbisi.
She was attending a celebration:

05:33.033 --> 05:34.535
a birth of a friend's baby.

05:34.568 --> 05:37.004
You know Mira well?
Mira's just
a customer.

05:37.037 --> 05:40.140
I like her. Her name in Arabic
means "princess,"

05:40.173 --> 05:42.376
like mine: Zara,
from the Hebrew.

05:42.410 --> 05:43.611
STABLER:
You Jewish?

05:43.644 --> 05:45.613
Oh, no, no. She's Muslim.

05:45.646 --> 05:48.882
ZARA:
The languages-- Arabic,
Hebrew dialects--

05:48.916 --> 05:50.017
they blend together.

05:50.050 --> 05:51.619
What's this all about?

05:51.652 --> 05:53.754
Do you know where
Mira's family lives?

05:53.787 --> 05:56.356
May I see your identification?

06:00.093 --> 06:03.897
Mira's husband
and his mother, Jazlyn--

06:03.931 --> 06:06.634
they publish The Arab-American,
the newspaper.

06:06.667 --> 06:09.069
It's around the corner
near the mosque.

06:10.438 --> 06:13.040
My wife? Haven't seen her
since last evening.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.041
She's with a friend.

06:14.074 --> 06:15.509
Which friend
would that be?

06:15.543 --> 06:17.044
Uh, my wife has
many friends.

06:17.077 --> 06:18.912
Are you two
not getting along?

06:18.946 --> 06:20.514
Of course we are.

06:20.548 --> 06:22.483
Mr. Elbisi,
is this your wife?

06:23.517 --> 06:24.652
Not to be rude, but it seems

06:24.685 --> 06:25.819
that if everything was fine,

06:25.853 --> 06:28.121
you'd know where
she spent the night.
Well, I tell you,

06:28.155 --> 06:30.157
you know what I find strange:
We ask you about your wife.

06:30.190 --> 06:32.059
You're not the least bit curious
why we're asking.

06:32.092 --> 06:33.527
Did she file a
new complaint,

06:33.561 --> 06:35.896
how I mistreat
and harass her?

06:35.929 --> 06:37.598
Why? You like to beat her up?

06:37.631 --> 06:39.600
I would never hurt Mira.
Where were you
last night?

06:39.633 --> 06:41.802
My mother and I worked
here late putting
the paper to bed.

06:41.835 --> 06:44.204
My mother's Jazlyn
Elbisi-- she's well-
known in the community.

06:44.237 --> 06:45.806
She here today?

06:45.839 --> 06:47.808
She took the day off.

06:47.841 --> 06:49.076
And how late did you two work?

06:49.109 --> 06:50.210
Mira doesn't
like being alone

06:50.243 --> 06:51.378
in the apartment
after dark.

06:51.411 --> 06:54.081
Sometimes she visits
friends in Bay Ridge
and stays over.

06:54.114 --> 06:55.115
Which friends?

06:56.850 --> 06:59.086
I-I don't know.

06:59.119 --> 07:01.221
Recognize this tattoo?

07:01.254 --> 07:04.992
Yes... and that mole.

07:05.993 --> 07:08.228
It's Mira.

07:08.261 --> 07:10.964
Why do you have
that photograph?

07:10.998 --> 07:14.234
Mr. Elbisi,
we're very sorry.

07:14.267 --> 07:16.570
Your wife was murdered
last night.

07:18.606 --> 07:19.707
No...

07:19.740 --> 07:21.709
STABLER:
She was burned to death.

07:21.742 --> 07:23.711
Who could've done this?

07:23.744 --> 07:26.580
We're hoping
you can help us with that.

07:26.614 --> 07:30.017
I wouldn't have any idea.

07:34.154 --> 07:37.124
JAZLYN:
Of course I was at the paper
with my son

07:37.157 --> 07:38.125
all evening.

07:38.158 --> 07:39.259
Could you translate
"evening"

07:39.292 --> 07:40.861
into something
more specific?

07:40.894 --> 07:43.597
I went to the office
around 5:00.

07:43.631 --> 07:44.798
I left at midnight.

07:44.832 --> 07:48.869
Your son told two detectives
that you left at, uh, 10:00 p.m.

07:48.902 --> 07:50.738
10:00, midnight.
It was a long day.

07:50.771 --> 07:51.972
What's the difference?

07:52.005 --> 07:54.141
The difference is
your stories don't match.

07:54.174 --> 07:55.876
Which probably means
you're not telling the truth.

07:55.909 --> 07:59.613
You just want to make Arabs
look like bad people.

07:59.647 --> 08:02.149
That's why you're here.

08:02.182 --> 08:03.884
All right.

08:03.917 --> 08:07.888
I came home with my grandson.

08:07.921 --> 08:09.890
I took him to the office,

08:09.923 --> 08:12.292
and I brought him home
to put him to bed.

08:12.325 --> 08:13.627
MUNCH:
Where was
his mother?

08:13.661 --> 08:14.895
I don't know.

08:14.928 --> 08:16.029
Nanna,

08:16.063 --> 08:17.765
where's Mama?

08:17.798 --> 08:20.534
When's Mama coming home?

08:24.905 --> 08:26.907
Sonny boy must've called Mom
and warned her.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.776
And they couldn't keep
their stories straight.

08:28.809 --> 08:30.310
Every word out of
her mouth was a lie,

08:30.343 --> 08:31.645
except maybe
"Good morning."

08:31.679 --> 08:32.913
Casey?

08:32.946 --> 08:35.616
Who talked to a reporter
about this burned woman?

08:35.649 --> 08:37.050
And it's nice to see you, too.

08:37.084 --> 08:39.620
"Burn Victim Said
To Be Target Of Hate Crime.

08:39.653 --> 08:41.655
"Sources say Special
Victims Unit detectives

08:41.689 --> 08:43.256
"refuse to release the
woman's ethnicity

08:43.290 --> 08:45.926
for fear of setting off
more attacks."

08:45.959 --> 08:47.861
I hope this didn't come
from here.

08:47.895 --> 08:49.196
We don't leak
to the press.

08:49.229 --> 08:51.665
Only person I talked
to about this was you.

08:51.699 --> 08:53.066
Well, then, how did
they get the story?

08:53.100 --> 08:54.201
Somebody heard
the rumor,

08:54.234 --> 08:56.169
made up the rest.
When this hits

08:56.203 --> 08:59.206
the papers before I brief
my boss, I look incompetent.

08:59.239 --> 09:02.676
Three weeks ago,
Mira Elbisi called the 7-4,

09:02.710 --> 09:04.077
said she was afraid
of her husband.

09:04.111 --> 09:06.079
Cops respond. She apologizes.

09:06.113 --> 09:07.347
She overreacted.

09:07.380 --> 09:09.216
One week later,
neighbor calls.

09:09.249 --> 09:10.483
Shouting from the Elbisi
apartment.

09:10.517 --> 09:12.820
This time, it was the mother-
in-law who sent the cops away.

09:12.853 --> 09:14.221
If he was abusing her,

09:14.254 --> 09:16.223
Mira had a lot of courage
calling the cops.

09:16.256 --> 09:17.357
Well, let's find this neighbor

09:17.390 --> 09:19.359
and see what the shouting
was about.

09:19.392 --> 09:20.961
I think maybe he hit her.

09:20.994 --> 09:22.362
She had a split lip
the next day.

09:22.395 --> 09:23.296
What were they
fighting about?

09:23.330 --> 09:25.098
I don't know.
Mira said she cut herself.

09:25.132 --> 09:25.899
I didn't believe her.

09:25.933 --> 09:26.967
Must have had a reason
for that.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.369
Well, she was struggling,
you know-- it was obvious.

09:29.402 --> 09:30.971
She had no one to talk to.

09:31.004 --> 09:32.706
She told me
she was true to Islam,

09:32.740 --> 09:34.842
but you could see
this lady wanted some freedom.

09:34.875 --> 09:36.243
STABLER:
You ever talk
to her husband?

09:36.276 --> 09:38.712
I don't go where I'm not wanted.

09:38.746 --> 09:40.113
Got a problem
with Arabs?

09:40.147 --> 09:43.717
No. He's got a problem with me.

09:43.751 --> 09:45.118
He's an educated guy.

09:45.152 --> 09:47.120
I think he looks down
on tradespeople.

09:47.154 --> 09:48.989
Did Mira fight with
her mother-in-law?

09:49.022 --> 09:50.991
She hated living
with the old lady.

09:51.024 --> 09:52.392
She felt squeezed.

09:52.425 --> 09:55.128
When they shouted,
they turned up the stereo.

09:55.162 --> 09:57.397
She ever mention anybody
that she confided in?

09:57.430 --> 09:59.266
There was one friend:
a guy who works

09:59.299 --> 10:01.268
for some do-gooder
religious group.

10:01.301 --> 10:03.136
He-he's Jewish.
She wanted me to meet him.

10:03.170 --> 10:06.006
Name's, uh, Feldman,
Joshua Feldman.

10:06.039 --> 10:08.909
She thought since I'm Jewish,
I'd make a donation.

10:11.178 --> 10:13.013
He beat her up, didn't he?

10:13.046 --> 10:14.147
That lunatic husband of hers.

10:14.181 --> 10:15.015
Is that why you're here?

10:15.048 --> 10:17.885
Mr. Feldman,
did you see Mira last night?

10:17.918 --> 10:19.753
Is she in the hospital?
Tell me.

10:19.787 --> 10:22.289
STABLER:
Was she here last night?
I was expecting her.

10:22.322 --> 10:24.758
We're trying to build
bridges here between
Muslims and Jews,

10:24.792 --> 10:26.293
and she wanted to
be a part of it.

10:26.326 --> 10:28.295
When she didn't
show up, I called.

10:28.328 --> 10:30.297
Her-her mother-in-law
answered, and I hung up.

10:30.330 --> 10:33.033
Why didn't you leave
a message?
Strange man calling

10:33.066 --> 10:35.736
a married Muslim woman
might not go over too well.

10:35.769 --> 10:37.037
So she kept her work here
secret?

10:37.070 --> 10:38.706
Yes.

10:38.739 --> 10:40.440
Mira's afraid her husband'll
keep her from coming.

10:40.473 --> 10:43.043
Please... tell me,
is she all right?

10:43.076 --> 10:45.178
Mr. Feldman...

10:45.212 --> 10:48.916
last night, Mira was attacked
two blocks from here.

10:48.949 --> 10:51.051
Maybe you read
today's paper?

10:51.084 --> 10:53.086
No...

10:55.088 --> 10:58.058
That was Mira?

10:58.091 --> 11:00.828
Oh, God, no...

11:01.829 --> 11:05.098
So, you two
were more than friends.

11:07.367 --> 11:10.037
We were in love.

11:10.070 --> 11:11.204
She was going to leave him.

11:11.238 --> 11:13.340
We were going to live together.

11:13.373 --> 11:15.743
Did her husband know
about all this?

11:15.776 --> 11:18.345
Yes. When she told him
I was Jewish,

11:18.378 --> 11:20.347
he said he'd never let her go,

11:20.380 --> 11:22.415
never let her leave.

11:31.358 --> 11:32.826
Mira and I fought.

11:32.860 --> 11:33.626
We argued.

11:33.660 --> 11:35.929
We're from
different generations.

11:35.963 --> 11:37.798
We didn't get along--
this was no secret.

11:37.831 --> 11:40.233
You sure had some secrets
last time we talked.

11:40.267 --> 11:42.202
Like where
your daughter-in-law was

11:42.235 --> 11:43.804
when you were
baby-sitting.

11:43.837 --> 11:45.138
I don't know.

11:45.172 --> 11:47.074
Your wife is out

11:47.107 --> 11:48.475
at night,
you have a young child,

11:48.508 --> 11:50.143
and you don't know where she is?

11:50.177 --> 11:51.812
She didn't
always tell me.

11:51.845 --> 11:52.980
I wonder why.

11:53.013 --> 11:54.381
I don't know
what you mean.

11:54.414 --> 11:56.349
I mean
her boyfriend.

11:56.383 --> 11:58.819
Please. My wife is dead.

11:58.852 --> 12:01.321
Don't defame her good name.

12:01.354 --> 12:05.158
Did you leave the newspaper
office at around 6:00

12:05.192 --> 12:07.060
with a can of fuel oil?

12:07.094 --> 12:09.329
We got a warrant,

12:09.362 --> 12:12.065
and we searched your car.

12:12.099 --> 12:15.335
Our lab found traces of oil
in your trunk.

12:15.368 --> 12:17.204
You want
to explain that?

12:18.205 --> 12:20.207
Our boiler in the office
went out.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.842
You need oil to prime it,

12:21.875 --> 12:24.244
and the service company
wouldn't come out,

12:24.277 --> 12:26.246
so we had to get some ourselves.

12:26.279 --> 12:28.181
We figure you
left your grandson

12:28.215 --> 12:31.251
at the office, and went out
with your son to start a fire.

12:31.284 --> 12:33.353
We're not barbarians.

12:33.386 --> 12:35.956
We are faithful Muslims.

12:35.989 --> 12:37.891
And you couldn't bear
that your daughter-in-law

12:37.925 --> 12:38.926
was in love with a Jew.

12:38.959 --> 12:41.094
AL-SHANI:
She cheated on me.

12:41.128 --> 12:47.334
She disgraced our family...
but I still loved her.

12:47.367 --> 12:49.870
Your wife wanted a divorce,
and you refused.

12:49.903 --> 12:51.471
Mira wanted to go,
she could go.

12:51.504 --> 12:53.373
Not if you threatened
to kill her.

12:53.406 --> 12:55.142
I would never do that.
Yeah, you would.

12:55.175 --> 12:56.844
The neighbor said
that you split her lip.

12:56.877 --> 12:57.845
It was an accident.

12:57.878 --> 12:58.846
We were both ill-tempered.

12:58.879 --> 12:59.947
That's not
what her boyfriend said.

12:59.980 --> 13:03.283
You see, Mr. Elbisi,
I want to believe you, I do...

13:03.316 --> 13:05.285
but you find out that your wife

13:05.318 --> 13:07.554
is having an affair
with a Jewish man,

13:07.587 --> 13:10.790
and I'm wondering how
somebody like you would react.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.929
Someone like me?

13:15.963 --> 13:18.531
He puts his head down.

13:18.565 --> 13:20.233
He cries.

13:20.267 --> 13:24.504
He mourns the loss of his son
because his wife gets custody.

13:24.537 --> 13:27.574
He doesn't set
the woman he loves on fire.

13:27.607 --> 13:30.443
Circumstantial-- unless
you get permission
to talk to his kid.

13:30.477 --> 13:32.579
A six-year-old
whose mother was just murdered?

13:32.612 --> 13:35.315
No judge will let us near him
unless we indict the father.

13:35.348 --> 13:36.616
Sure we got the
right people?

13:36.649 --> 13:37.918
Yeah. Why?

13:37.951 --> 13:39.186
Then we got a copycat.

13:39.219 --> 13:40.187
NOVAK:
What?

13:40.220 --> 13:41.454
94th Street and Second Avenue,

13:41.488 --> 13:42.455
near the big mosque.

13:42.489 --> 13:43.456
A man set on fire.

13:43.490 --> 13:45.292
Name was Tariq
Assad, 27.

13:45.325 --> 13:47.027
Didn't live
to make it to
the ambulance,

13:47.060 --> 13:49.129
but we got a witness.

13:49.162 --> 13:50.597
BENSON:
The witness is
Jason Mullavy.

13:50.630 --> 13:52.432
Says the guy in flames
came toward him,

13:52.465 --> 13:53.533
and he heard
somebody shouting,

13:53.566 --> 13:56.269
"Killer, you'll
burn in hell for
what you did to us!"

13:56.303 --> 13:58.638
Just what the city needs
to read in tomorrow's papers.

13:58.671 --> 13:59.907
Mr. Mullavy?

13:59.940 --> 14:01.274
Jason,
Captain Cragen.

14:01.308 --> 14:02.575
How you doing?

14:02.609 --> 14:03.944
